Html:
Rest parameters can be used in constructor functions, but the syntax currenty is<br />
<pre><code>class Foo {
    constructor (...private rest: number[]) {}
}</code></pre>

To me, the following would feel more natural, so I'd like to start a discussion on it (though there certainly is nothing &quot;wrong&quot; with the current behavior):<br />
<pre><code>class Foo {
    constructor (private ...rest: number[]) {}
}</code></pre>
